Richie Benaud was farewelled at a small family funeral in Sydney on Wednesday . 
  The cricketing legend was offered a state funeral by Prime Minister Tony Abbott . 
  His wife Daphne and brother John Benaud were the only immediate family members to attend . 
  The 84-year-old former Test captain was to be farewelled by a group of just 12 people . 
  The private service was organised by his wife and was held in Sydney's eastern suburbs . 
  Fellow commentators and cricketing greats attended the service . 
 